   MODES AND GYROSCOPES
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The Hubble Space Telescope was awakened from its self-induced sleep on Apr. 28, 1990 but it was still without the use of its high-speed antennas, and its science instruments were on hold, unable to begin any observations.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The telescope's big eye has remained open, but Hubble had been in a "safe mode" with all motion stopped because of earlier problems in linking the high-speed dish antennas with a relay satellite.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Terry said the telescope was running on a "normal control-all mode," where its own computers and sensors guide where it is pointing.
  </a>
